item.description: Basic Information USU, CEHS graduate student’s 1st course in quantitative methods Held: Spring Semester 2018, Tues and Thursday 4:40-5:45pm Cross listed as Psy 6600 and Educ 6600 Students may attend at the Logan campus or at a USU distance site Course Purpose Research Design & Analysis I is designed to provide the student with a practical, applied approach to the application of fundamental behavioral and educational research design and statistical principles.
